<!--Extra announcement-->

<p>I hope you guys are having fun planning your white water rafting site! After speaking with a student, I noticed there is an error in the course code. If you want to change your paragraph text on white to a color other than black, you won't be able to.</p>
<p>Unfortunately as an instructor I am unable to fix the error - only course creators have the ability to do that. I'm submitting a course correction so that it does get fixed, but in the mean time, here is a little video teaching you how to make the fix yourself so that you can change your paragraph colors.</p>
<div style="position: relative; padding-bottom: 62.5%; height: 0;"><iframe style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;" src="https://www.loom.com/embed/3249d2ab6a9f46bd8d415e8d79f75b05" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitallowfullscreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen"></iframe></div>
<p>If you are unable to watch the video, just know you will need to change line 59 of your code to:</p>
<p>color: var(--paragraph-color-on-white);</p>
<p>instead of</p>
<p>color: var(--paragraph-color);</p>
<p><span style="font-size: 18pt;"><strong>Extra Typography Help</strong></span></p>
<p><span style="font-size: 12pt;">I also noticed that the instructions don't go into full detail about how to change the fonts. In step 10 of the assignment the instructions show you how to change the fonts in your import, but not on your webpage. Here's how to do it:</span></p>
<div style="position: relative; padding-bottom: 62.5%; height: 0;"><iframe style="position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; width: 100%; height: 100%;" src="https://www.loom.com/embed/098b16e721e14f058e86512896b7facc" allowfullscreen="allowfullscreen" webkitallowfullscreen="webkitallowfullscreen" mozallowfullscreen="mozallowfullscreen"></iframe></div>
<p>If you are unable to watch the video, you will need to change the variables --heading-font and --paragraph-font on lines 14 and 15 to have your new font.&nbsp;</p>
<p>As an example, I wanted to use montserrat for my paragraph so I changed the variable from:</p>
<p>--paragraph-font: Lato, Helvetica, sans-serif;</p>
<p>to :</p>
<p>--paragraph-font: Montserrat, Helvetica, sans-serif;</p>
